Prototypical Nephele job that accepts a video stream, decodes it, manipulates the
decoded frames and reencodes the data.

=== Requirements ===
* Maven
* Nephele 0.2 (not officially released) 
 * get it from git@cit-server.cit.tu-berlin.de:stratosphere.git
 * checkout streaming branch
 * In stratosphere/nephele execute 'mvn install -Dmaven.test.skip=true' to install to local repository
* Maven Dependencies (maven will take care of these)


=== How to build ===
Run 'mvn package' to compile. Produces a jar file in target/ directory.


=== How to run ===
1) Start Nephele job manager (from git@cit-server.cit.tu-berlin.de:stratosphere.git streaming branch)

2) Run one of the Job classes:
 * de.tuberlin.cit.livescale.CitstreamerPrototypeJob
 * de.tuberlin.cit.livescale.Job
 * de.tuberlin.cit.livescale.JobWithFileInput
 * de.tuberlin.cit.livescale.ParallelJob

3) Simulate a phone dumping video into the workflow (optional)
 * de.tuberlin.cit.livescale.client.LivestreamClient
 ** needs configuration in livescaleclient.properties 

==== Structure ===
Consists of:

* Several Nephele Jobs in de.tuberlin.cit.livescale (classes with main())

* Livestream client that simulates a phone dumping video into a Nephele workflow
** can be configured with livescaleclient.properties

* other stuff used for some experiments (not important)
